<?php
$page_title = "About";
$content = <<<EOD

<script type="text/javascript">
var click_handler = function () {
   // Create the iframe we will drop in
   var iframe = document.createElement("iframe");
   iframe.src = "http://webchat.freenode.net?randomnick=1&channels=%23%23openhatch&uio=d4";
   iframe.width = "640";
   iframe.height = "400";

   // Find the element to replace
   var p = document.getElementById('click_to_webchat');
   if ( p === null ) {
        return false;
   }
    
   // Do the replacement
   p.parentNode.replaceChild(iframe, p);

   // return false, indicating that event propagation should stop
   return false;
}

// Bind it to our favorite link
var bind_click_handler = function () {
    $('#click_to_webchat a').click(click_handler);
}

// Bind it at page load
$(bind_click_handler);
</script>

<h2>Who Asheesh is</h2>

<p><img src="images/asheesh.jpg" width="180" class="alignleft" /> <a href="http://openhatch.org/people/paulproteus/">Asheesh Laroia</a> is the co-founder and lead developer of <a href="http://openhatch.org">OpenHatch</a> and a Developer in <a href="http://www.debian.org">Debian</a>. He has also engineered software at <a href="http://creativecommons.org">Creative Commons</a> in San Francisco and worked on Python-based video sharing site <a href="http://www.mirocommunity.org/">Miro Community</a> for the <a href="http://pculture.org">Participatory Culture Foundation</a> in New York City. He has given talks on FOSS mentorship, community-building, and outreach at several open source software conferences including <a href="http://blip.tv/pycon-us-videos-2009-2010-2011/pycon-2011-get-new-contributors-and-diversity-through-outreach-4898684">PyCon</a> and <a href="http://penta.debconf.org/dc11_schedule/events/778.en.html">DebConf</a>. s

<p>Asheesh is currently based in Boston, MA but regularly travels all over the place. <a href="mailto:asheesh@openhatch.org">Ask Asheesh to run an Open Source Comes to Campus event at your school!</a></p>

<h2>What OpenHatch is</h2>

<p>OpenHatch is an open source community aiming to help newcomers find their way into free software projects. We work toward this goal by developing useful web tools for new contributors and leading in-person outreach events.</p>

<h2>Get in touch</h2>

<p>Curious about running an Open Source Comes to Campus event on your campus? Want to bring Asheesh out to run one for you? Email us at <a href="mailto:events@lists.openhatch.org">events@lists.openhatch.org</a>.</p>

<p>Want to chat ahead of an event? Have other questions? Ask questions on the #openhatch channel on FreeNode, below. Consider using IRC your first open source accomplishment :)</p>

<div style="height: 400;">
<p id="click_to_webchat" style="margin-top: 50px;"><a href="#" onclick="click_handler();">Click here to chat on IRC within this web page</a></p>
</div>

EOD;

require_once("template.php");
?>
